[[div class="darkpanel duplo storm" style="width:95%;margin: 0 auto; border-width: 0.05rem 0.75rem 0.05rem 0.75rem; border-color:rgb(33, 33, 33);"]]
= [[size 125%]][[span class="VT323"]]THE MAUVe SYSTEM[[/span]][[/size]]
-----
[[div style="width:600px;margin:0 auto;display:block;position:relative;"]]
[[f>image mauvef.png width="600px"]]
----
[[=]]
[[size 80%]]{{One databank of the MAUVe system.}}[[/size]]
[[/=]]
[[/div]]
MAUVe was conceptualized in May of 2006, proposed as a means to provide instantaneous and fully accurate measurements of physical space, free from distortions caused by various factors such as [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boundary_problem_(spatial_analysis) boundary phenomena]. This could then be used by the Department of Topology to accurately identify and model complex structures, up to and including those within higher dimensions.

MAUVe's internal construction included remote viewing arcanotechnology, several highly advanced QCDOC-based supercomputers,[[footnote]]Quantum chromodynamics on a chip technology enables computation of small but extremely demanding calculations via use of specialized nodes arranged in a [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QCDOC sixth dimensional toroidal lattice].[[/footnote]] an array of measuring instruments and internal support systems supplemented by a self-modular additive manufacturing complex,[[footnote]]Essentially, the MAUVe system contains its own printing bay, which enables self-modification and iteration upon existing architecture with the goal of increasingly accurate apparati.[[/footnote]] and a biomechanical, artificially-intelligent conscript, Enkidu.aic, previously associated with Site-43's Quantum Supermechanics Department, to assist in the analysis and reasoning of large datasets.
@@ @@
[[/div]]
@@ @@
@@ @@
@@ @@
[[div class="oheader slim gray medium opaque" style="border:2px solid black;font-weight:600;"]]
[[span class="VT323" style="font-size: 1.3em;font-weight:400;"]]UPDATE 8882-0-05-01[[/span]]
----
The MAUVe system was completed in September of 2047, however, its usage would not occur for another six months; while running first-time calibrations, Enkidu.aic initiated the first of multiple redesigns of its own internal measuring equipment, as was expected. Upon completion, the Department of Topology began a series of control experiments, the results of which follow:
[[/div]]
